1
00:00:05,021 --> 00:00:12,144
Ajñāta sukṛti means: an unknowing
connection with the nirguṇa plane.

2
00:00:12,236 --> 00:00:14,785
[Faith | Possible Impossible]

3
00:00:14,955 --> 00:00:18,631
Guru Mahārāj told,
when a man is lying unconscious,

4
00:00:18,631 --> 00:00:20,424
we see in the modern world,
the paramedics come

5
00:00:20,424 --> 00:00:23,386
and they inject him
with something

6
00:00:23,386 --> 00:00:25,303
to bring him
to consciousness,

7
00:00:25,303 --> 00:00:27,431
and they say, 
“Can you hear me?

8
00:00:27,431 --> 00:00:31,507
If you can hear me—
move your finger or move your arm,

9
00:00:31,507 --> 00:00:33,550
give some indication
you can hear me.”

10
00:00:33,550 --> 00:00:35,090
Then when they do that,

11
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:38,693
then, now they’re jñāta,
awakened;

12
00:00:38,693 --> 00:00:41,592
they can begin to cooperate
for their own betterment.

13
00:00:41,854 --> 00:00:45,333
Jñāta sukṛti leads to what?

14
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:52,291
‘Śraddhā’-śabde—viśvāsa kahe
sudṛḍha niśchaya 
[Cc: Madhya, 2.22.62].

15
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:55,145
What is śraddhā, minimally?

16
00:00:55,145 --> 00:00:58,091
You hear about Kṛṣṇa consciousness
and think,

17
00:00:58,091 --> 00:01:00,717
“It’s possible!

18
00:01:00,717 --> 00:01:02,920
I can’t understand
everything they’re saying,

19
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:07,506
but there’s something there
that sounds possible.”

20
00:01:08,275 --> 00:01:12,590
That affirmative affirmation,

21
00:01:12,590 --> 00:01:19,777
just a positive heart expression
towards what has been heard;

22
00:01:19,777 --> 00:01:24,840
śraddhā, a belief in a more
cultured way that

23
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:27,950
if I just pursue this—

24
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:36,090
yasmin vijñāte sarvam evaṁ
vijñātaṁ bhavati 
[Mu: 1.3],

25
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:40,964
inquire about that one thing,
knowing which everything is known;

26
00:01:40,964 --> 00:01:45,350
try for that one thing, having obtained,
everything is got.

27
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:49,539
Yaṁ labdhvā chāparaṁ lābhaṁ
manyate nādhikaṁ tataḥ 
[Bg: 6.22],

28
00:01:49,539 --> 00:01:51,789
in the samādhi chapter
in Bhagavad-gītā …

29
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:54,323
What is it really,
when you’re in connection with this?
 

30
00:01:54,323 --> 00:01:58,840
See, it’s consistent to Kavirāj Goswāmī’s
śraddhā explanation:

31
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:01,108
coming in connection with this,
you think you’ve got everything.

32
00:02:01,108 --> 00:02:03,443
Rukmiṇī, again in the Bhāgavatam,

33
00:02:03,443 --> 00:02:06,531
“Rūpaṁ dṛśāṁ dṛśimatām
akhilārtha-lābhaṁ” 
[SB: 10.52.37],

34
00:02:06,531 --> 00:02:08,717
“Now I think I’ve got everything.”

35
00:02:08,717 --> 00:02:12,340
It’s a consistent thread throughout.

36
00:02:13,323 --> 00:02:16,924
That’s faith, belief; “Yes,

37
00:02:16,924 --> 00:02:18,007
goptṛtve varaṇaṁ 
[Cc: Madhya, 2.22.100],

38
00:02:18,007 --> 00:02:21,396
I’ll just give myself to Kṛṣṇa,

39
00:02:21,396 --> 00:02:25,183
He’ll protect me, maintain me.”

40
00:02:25,183 --> 00:02:29,529
Have to have some belief
in that possibility. Śraddhā.

